WEBVTT

00:00:08.263 --> 00:00:11.558
Now honor our sulphurous
contract... writ in blood...!

00:00:13.268 --> 00:00:15.395
Let the ebon
flames burn black...!

00:00:15.395 --> 00:00:21.151
Fulfill my wish, O beast!

00:00:21.151 --> 00:00:22.486
Ahhhhh!

00:00:22.486 --> 00:00:24.947
How'm I gonna heat up
my chicken tenders now...?!

00:00:24.947 --> 00:00:27.699
You can expect this level
of disregard for your things.

00:00:27.699 --> 00:00:29.993
You might wanna run for it.

00:00:29.993 --> 00:00:31.119
Don't be a butthead...!

00:00:31.119 --> 00:00:32.788
You should say
that you're sorry--

00:00:32.788 --> 00:00:34.706
then go out and buy
me a new microwave!

00:00:34.706 --> 00:00:36.792
Surely not in this economy?

00:00:37.918 --> 00:00:40.379
No photographs...!
I was very clear on that!

00:00:40.379 --> 00:00:42.005
A keepsake.

00:00:42.005 --> 00:00:42.714
Huh?

00:00:42.714 --> 00:00:45.384
Shining Finger!

00:00:45.384 --> 00:00:47.594
Check it, ladies, the
upgrade is complete...!

00:00:47.594 --> 00:00:51.890
Phone Wave Mark II Version 1.03
is ready to rock your world...!

00:00:51.890 --> 00:00:54.101
Thanks to the heroic
efforts of yours truly,

00:00:54.101 --> 00:00:56.770
we can now shuttle D-mail
to any number we feel like!

00:00:56.770 --> 00:00:58.522
Excellent work, my friend!

00:00:58.522 --> 00:01:01.149
We should get back to
the experiments, then!

00:01:01.149 --> 00:01:03.527
Is it really a... time machine?

00:01:03.527 --> 00:01:05.654
You're not to breathe
a word of it to anyone.

00:01:06.446 --> 00:01:09.616
I sure do hope Mr. Prawn
doesn't get mad at us again...

00:01:11.326 --> 00:01:12.661
Part-time girl!

00:01:12.661 --> 00:01:14.037
Hello down there!

00:01:14.037 --> 00:01:14.496
Hi!

00:01:14.496 --> 00:01:15.789
This is no time for too-too-!

00:01:15.789 --> 00:01:18.333
Where's... Mr. Braun?!

00:01:18.333 --> 00:01:18.917
Who's that?

00:01:18.917 --> 00:01:20.460
Daddy's name
isn't Mr. Braun...

00:01:20.460 --> 00:01:22.254
Oh, you're talking
'bout the big boss-man.

00:01:22.254 --> 00:01:23.672
I think he's been
out on a house-call

00:01:23.672 --> 00:01:24.548
for most of the afternoon.

00:01:24.548 --> 00:01:25.382
House call?

00:01:25.382 --> 00:01:27.342
Why you think I'm
fiddling with my bike?

00:01:34.099 --> 00:01:35.267
Now, Mayuri.

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:43.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:52.451 --> 00:01:53.827
It's real!

00:01:53.827 --> 00:01:56.246
Hey... what was that...?

00:03:35.220 --> 00:03:37.305
I betcha some
juicy chicken tenders

00:03:37.305 --> 00:03:39.850
would go really
well with all this...

00:03:39.850 --> 00:03:43.353
Huh? Hold on...!
Where's the bag with my soda?!

00:03:43.353 --> 00:03:44.563
Sorry. Sold out.

00:03:44.563 --> 00:03:47.190
Then you beat a path from
store to store till you find it!

00:03:47.190 --> 00:03:50.235
I wouldn't have to explain this
to an assistant worth her salt!

00:03:50.235 --> 00:03:53.113
I'm not gonna schlep all over
town just to get you soda...!

00:03:53.113 --> 00:03:55.198
Here.

00:03:57.659 --> 00:03:58.952
Hand it over...

00:03:58.952 --> 00:04:00.078
I'm a mad scientist,

00:04:00.078 --> 00:04:03.248
not some shriveled octogenarian
mewling about his fiber intake.

00:04:06.626 --> 00:04:08.378
Let the round
table now assemble!

00:04:08.378 --> 00:04:10.755
Just a sec, man--I'm
gettin' the sweats.

00:04:10.755 --> 00:04:12.716
What in the nine hells do
you think you're doing...?!

00:04:12.716 --> 00:04:14.593
You want the
Organization to hear this?

00:04:14.593 --> 00:04:15.886
Why not invite them in?

00:04:15.886 --> 00:04:17.095
Yeah, whatever.

00:04:22.726 --> 00:04:24.561
Starting now, Operation Wyrd

00:04:24.561 --> 00:04:26.730
goes into the second
phase of experimentation...

00:04:26.730 --> 00:04:30.901
which will allow us...
to gauge D-mail's effect.

00:04:30.901 --> 00:04:32.736
Barley tea's so
good in the summer...!

00:04:32.736 --> 00:04:34.404
You want some, Moeka?

00:04:34.404 --> 00:04:38.575
Okay, so what kind of
experiments are you thinkin' of?

00:04:38.575 --> 00:04:40.660
We are going to change the past.

00:04:43.663 --> 00:04:46.333
No way. We are not taking
that kind of risk...!

00:04:46.333 --> 00:04:48.251
What if it results
in a time paradox?

00:04:48.251 --> 00:04:49.169
Then so be it...!

00:04:49.169 --> 00:04:51.588
Any true mad scientist
would absolutely kill

00:04:51.588 --> 00:04:53.340
to know if D-mails can
really alter the past.

00:04:53.340 --> 00:04:55.050
You disappoint me, Assistant.

00:04:55.050 --> 00:04:56.510
I... I just think...

00:04:56.510 --> 00:04:58.386
How are you gonna
prove it, Okarin?

00:04:58.386 --> 00:05:00.013
Thank you so much for asking.

00:05:00.013 --> 00:05:01.306
By virtue of a single event,

00:05:01.306 --> 00:05:03.767
the occurrence of
which will brook no doubt.

00:05:06.645 --> 00:05:08.939
Picking the winning
numbers in the lottery!

00:05:11.650 --> 00:05:14.236
Okarin... I'm
disappointed in you.

00:05:14.236 --> 00:05:16.863
Dude, sick! I'm totally
rollin' up to the curb

00:05:16.863 --> 00:05:18.823
at Queen May's in the earthbound
equivalent of a Star Destroyer!

00:05:18.823 --> 00:05:20.200
Instead of being Greedy Gus'es,

00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:21.368
wouldn't it be a lot nicer

00:05:21.368 --> 00:05:22.994
if we tried to make
world peace happen...?

00:05:22.994 --> 00:05:26.248
We could give everyone
on Earth an oopa cushion!

00:05:26.248 --> 00:05:29.668
Seriously, man...
Way to be a total jackass.

00:05:29.668 --> 00:05:32.254
I'm trying to see if I can alter
the blasted past, woman...!

00:05:32.254 --> 00:05:33.922
We need a quantifiable change!

00:05:33.922 --> 00:05:35.757
And that's the first
thing you could think of?

00:05:35.757 --> 00:05:37.175
Quiet, Little Miss Moneybags!

00:05:37.175 --> 00:05:39.886
"Moneybags"...? What the hell?!

00:05:39.886 --> 00:05:41.429
Well that's what
you really are...!

00:05:41.429 --> 00:05:44.099
Lounging in some
opulent hotel room

00:05:44.099 --> 00:05:45.308
your parents are paying for...!

00:05:45.308 --> 00:05:47.477
"Let them eat cake!"
eh there, Antoinette!?

00:05:47.477 --> 00:05:49.521
Don't you have a lotto to fix?

00:05:49.521 --> 00:05:51.439
Makise's right.
We should figure that out.

00:05:51.439 --> 00:05:53.859
Which one should we win, though?

00:05:53.859 --> 00:05:56.903
Which one, indeed...

00:05:56.903 --> 00:05:58.154
What's the matter?

00:05:58.154 --> 00:05:59.364
Not sure...

00:06:01.491 --> 00:06:03.326
Where is Double-O Five?

00:06:03.326 --> 00:06:04.536
Dunno.

00:06:06.329 --> 00:06:08.164
What're you doing?!

00:06:08.164 --> 00:06:09.708
There ya go.

00:06:09.708 --> 00:06:12.210
Can't take my eyes off of
you for a second, can I?

00:06:12.210 --> 00:06:14.588
I texted... You never replied.

00:06:18.174 --> 00:06:21.261
Dude, smoking hot aside,
what a space-cadet.

00:06:21.261 --> 00:06:22.053
Christina!

00:06:22.053 --> 00:06:23.471
You are hereby tasked

00:06:23.471 --> 00:06:24.889
with preventing her
from wandering off!

00:06:24.889 --> 00:06:29.144
Huh...?! Hey!
I'm not your guard dog.

00:06:29.144 --> 00:06:31.688
Poor Moeka, stuck on the couch.

00:06:31.688 --> 00:06:33.898
Would you like me to give
you the grand tour of the lab?

00:06:33.898 --> 00:06:35.692
It really is a
whole lot of fun...!

00:06:35.692 --> 00:06:39.446
If you don't believe
me, just ask Kurisu!

00:06:39.446 --> 00:06:43.366
Hmmm... now where to start...

00:06:43.366 --> 00:06:46.411
How 'bout the Lotto 6?
It looks juicy.

00:06:47.537 --> 00:06:50.165
They've just announced
this week's winning numbers.

00:06:50.165 --> 00:06:53.209
So now we send them into the
past... and see what happens.

00:06:53.209 --> 00:06:54.628
You're really going to do this?

00:06:54.628 --> 00:06:56.588
If you've a better
idea, speak up!

00:06:57.422 --> 00:06:59.883
The numbers're right here,
so we can do it whenever...

00:06:59.883 --> 00:07:05.388
Looks like the current jackpot's
at... Two-hundred million!

00:07:05.388 --> 00:07:06.389
Two... hundred million...?!

00:07:06.389 --> 00:07:07.849
Whoa, Daru! Hold on...!

00:07:07.849 --> 00:07:09.184
That's a little much, yeah...?

00:07:09.184 --> 00:07:09.643
Say wha?

00:07:09.643 --> 00:07:12.395
Well... hitting a jackpot of
that size would only serve...

00:07:12.395 --> 00:07:15.106
to... draw unwanted
attention to ourselv--

00:07:15.106 --> 00:07:16.232
What a total chicken.

00:07:16.232 --> 00:07:17.692
Second prize?!

00:07:17.692 --> 00:07:20.362
Oh, good call. Only 23 million.

00:07:20.362 --> 00:07:21.529
What's third?!

00:07:21.529 --> 00:07:22.072
Seven-hundred thousand.

00:07:22.072 --> 00:07:24.991
Perfect-that-one-yes!

00:07:24.991 --> 00:07:26.785
Good form there,
fearless leader.

00:07:26.785 --> 00:07:28.703
This from the girl who's
quailing in her boots

00:07:28.703 --> 00:07:29.412
at the thought--

00:07:29.412 --> 00:07:30.121
This is an oopa cushion!

00:07:30.121 --> 00:07:31.456
If you ever feel oogy

00:07:31.456 --> 00:07:32.707
and you need to
some cheering up...

00:07:32.707 --> 00:07:36.002
just-give-'em a big hug!

00:07:36.002 --> 00:07:38.672
Next stop! The lab refrigerator!

00:07:38.672 --> 00:07:41.549
What's inside you today...?

00:07:41.549 --> 00:07:43.176
May I...?

00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:53.853
Time to earn your
keep, Double-O Five.

00:07:53.853 --> 00:07:57.691
Here's your first Future
Gadget Lab assignment.

00:07:57.691 --> 00:07:59.776
Oh! This is exciting!

00:07:59.776 --> 00:08:02.404
I would like you to compose
the D-mail message...

00:08:02.404 --> 00:08:05.115
Something that will convince
the ignorant me of a week ago

00:08:05.115 --> 00:08:07.951
to buy a ticket with the
number we've provided.

00:08:09.411 --> 00:08:14.582
Seven days is...
168 hours. Cool if I round up?

00:08:14.582 --> 00:08:16.126
That'll do.

00:08:16.126 --> 00:08:17.585
Short and sweet.

00:08:17.585 --> 00:08:18.920
Okay. Ready when you are.

00:08:18.920 --> 00:08:22.882
Stein's Gate will finally
swing open to admit me!

00:08:22.882 --> 00:08:25.385
Not that again.
Give the crazy the day off.

00:08:25.385 --> 00:08:28.221
You're remarkably
close-minded for a scientist!

00:08:31.641 --> 00:08:34.227
You looked like you
were... both having fun.

00:08:34.227 --> 00:08:34.477
Fun?

00:08:34.477 --> 00:08:36.688
Dealing with this nut-case?!

00:08:36.688 --> 00:08:39.232
They're the OTP in the
fan-fic I call my life...

00:08:39.232 --> 00:08:40.567
We are not OTP!

00:08:40.567 --> 00:08:44.029
Oh...! So you know the jargon
of the fan-fic community...!

00:08:44.029 --> 00:08:46.740
Huh...?! I don't know
what you're talking about!

00:08:46.740 --> 00:08:48.491
It rolled off your
tongue so naturally...

00:08:48.491 --> 00:08:51.494
Look. If we're gonna
do this, let's do it!

00:08:52.495 --> 00:08:55.373
'Kay, everybody--I'm getting
ready to fire up the Phone Wave!

00:09:10.513 --> 00:09:12.432
We are not taking
that kind of risk...!

00:09:12.432 --> 00:09:15.351
What if it results
in a time paradox?

00:09:17.812 --> 00:09:21.024
Come on...!
Fortune favors the bold!

00:09:27.530 --> 00:09:30.658
El... Psy... Congroo!

00:09:48.551 --> 00:09:56.559
Okarin...Okarin...!
Hey, are you in there...?

00:09:59.896 --> 00:10:01.523
Are you okay...?

00:10:01.523 --> 00:10:03.316
I... I don't know...

00:10:07.821 --> 00:10:10.990
How long... how long have
I just been standing here?

00:10:10.990 --> 00:10:14.369
Um... about 30 seconds, I guess.

00:10:14.369 --> 00:10:16.120
I actually lost
half a minute...?

00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:17.372
You don't remember anything...?

00:10:17.372 --> 00:10:19.666
We were talking about
what D-mail we should send

00:10:19.666 --> 00:10:21.668
to see if it would really
alter the world line...

00:10:21.668 --> 00:10:22.627
Then all of a sudden...

00:10:22.627 --> 00:10:24.128
You rushed over
to the Phone Wave

00:10:24.128 --> 00:10:26.673
and you went,
"hahhauah" all breathy-like.

00:10:26.673 --> 00:10:28.883
Hey Mayushii--do that
breathy thing again, yeah?

00:10:28.883 --> 00:10:30.218
Oh give it a rest, Daru!

00:10:30.218 --> 00:10:31.427
Sorry.

00:10:42.564 --> 00:10:44.232
It arrived...

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:48.027
Are you sure
you're feeling okay?

00:10:48.027 --> 00:10:50.655
What about the money?!
From the lotto ticket...!

00:10:50.655 --> 00:10:52.991
Did we win third prize,
Christina?! Tell me!

00:10:52.991 --> 00:10:56.870
Stop calling me that...!
Wait... what ticket?

00:10:56.870 --> 00:10:59.539
You really, don't know
what I'm talking about?!

00:10:59.539 --> 00:11:01.875
I'm confused...

00:11:01.875 --> 00:11:02.959
For the lottery...!

00:11:02.959 --> 00:11:04.752
Our experiment
to change the past!

00:11:04.752 --> 00:11:06.045
Sending back a D-mail!

00:11:06.045 --> 00:11:07.922
Stop acting like such a spaz!

00:11:07.922 --> 00:11:10.425
We haven't come up with
a message to send back yet!

00:11:10.425 --> 00:11:10.800
What...?

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:14.262
Wouldn't it be nice if we tried
to make world peace happen?

00:11:14.262 --> 00:11:16.681
We could give everyone
on Earth an oopa cushion!

00:11:16.681 --> 00:11:19.684
They really don't...
remember it at all...

00:11:22.729 --> 00:11:24.772
It's open!

00:11:26.900 --> 00:11:29.193
Oh! Hey, Ruka! Come on in!

00:11:33.281 --> 00:11:35.658
I hope that you can
forgive me, Kyouma!

00:11:35.658 --> 00:11:37.368
What...? Why?

00:11:37.368 --> 00:11:38.453
Here...

00:11:39.495 --> 00:11:42.874
Oh-two... and
twelve... eighteen...

00:11:42.874 --> 00:11:45.001
an' all the rest... Rukako!

00:11:45.001 --> 00:11:46.753
How'd you come up
with these numbers?!

00:11:46.753 --> 00:11:49.422
Um... well I... tried
to buy a lottery ticket

00:11:49.422 --> 00:11:51.257
using the numbers you gave me...

00:11:51.257 --> 00:11:52.217
Come again...?!

00:11:52.217 --> 00:11:53.718
You said I should
play those numbers

00:11:53.718 --> 00:11:55.887
because they were lucky
or something, so I tried...

00:11:55.887 --> 00:11:57.388
That... was when?

00:11:57.388 --> 00:11:59.140
Guess it's been
about a week now?

00:11:59.140 --> 00:12:01.893
Omigosh, is your
brain psychic, Okarin?

00:12:01.893 --> 00:12:04.646
So, are we winner-winner-
chicken-dinner or what?

00:12:04.646 --> 00:12:05.813
That's the thing...

00:12:05.813 --> 00:12:08.608
I got one of the numbers
all turned around in my head.

00:12:08.608 --> 00:12:10.109
Huh...?!

00:12:12.153 --> 00:12:14.072
Aw, you were so close, dude!

00:12:14.072 --> 00:12:15.823
Man, that sucks!

00:12:15.823 --> 00:12:19.869
Okabe... did you use the
Phone Wave to do this...?

00:12:23.539 --> 00:12:25.124
Where's the bag with my soda?!

00:12:25.124 --> 00:12:28.294
I'm not gonna schlep all over
town just to get you soda!

00:12:36.094 --> 00:12:38.096
There's no doubt in
my mind that I sent it.

00:12:39.013 --> 00:12:42.558
Nothing...
Like it never existed.

00:12:42.558 --> 00:12:46.854
Perhaps... my actions
have rewritten the past.

00:12:46.854 --> 00:12:50.108
They've no memory
of the experiment.

00:12:50.108 --> 00:12:53.069
We discussed it and
carried it out together.

00:12:53.069 --> 00:12:55.405
No one else remembers it.

00:12:56.406 --> 00:12:59.158
I'm the only one.

00:12:59.158 --> 00:13:00.910
This feels just like that day.

00:13:04.706 --> 00:13:06.541
Come on... think...

00:13:13.423 --> 00:13:15.091
Whatcha looking at?

00:13:17.552 --> 00:13:19.429
Something important to me.

00:13:26.894 --> 00:13:28.062
You okay?

00:13:30.106 --> 00:13:32.942
You look like,
you've been brainwashed.

00:13:32.942 --> 00:13:37.613
I, look that rough?
Hell... Maybe I was.

00:13:37.613 --> 00:13:39.115
A bit of brainwashing
would certainly

00:13:39.115 --> 00:13:42.702
explain whatever's
going on--What the hell?!

00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:54.464
You haven't been chipped.

00:13:54.464 --> 00:13:55.465
Uhhh...

00:13:55.465 --> 00:13:58.342
Whatever it is,
nobody's brainwashed you.

00:13:58.342 --> 00:14:00.636
Good... to know...?

00:14:00.636 --> 00:14:03.181
Hey, how do you wash your brain?

00:14:03.181 --> 00:14:04.640
Well...

00:14:04.640 --> 00:14:09.270
A mad scientist like yours truly
would be happy to explain it.

00:14:09.270 --> 00:14:12.607
Maybe we'll hold off 'til she's
a little less afraid of you.

00:14:14.484 --> 00:14:16.778
There's something
I have to know.

00:14:21.032 --> 00:14:21.783
Tremor, huh?

00:14:21.783 --> 00:14:23.493
There was one a
while back, I know that.

00:14:23.493 --> 00:14:25.203
The shop was
shaking pretty heavy.

00:14:25.203 --> 00:14:27.830
You should have felt
another about ten minutes ago.

00:14:27.830 --> 00:14:30.041
Nope. Dunno how
I could have missed it.

00:14:30.041 --> 00:14:30.958
You feel it?

00:14:30.958 --> 00:14:32.168
Nope.

00:14:33.836 --> 00:14:35.838
Could you be any
more of a perv?!

00:14:35.838 --> 00:14:37.215
C'mon, they stick out...!

00:14:37.215 --> 00:14:39.634
Nature wants me to look at 'em!

00:14:39.634 --> 00:14:42.387
See? I told ya it's easy
to hear what's going on.

00:14:42.387 --> 00:14:44.138
So ungodly loud...!

00:14:44.138 --> 00:14:47.767
Did you hear us going on
about the time machines, also?!

00:14:47.767 --> 00:14:49.602
Mm-hmm! That was
super interesting.

00:14:49.602 --> 00:14:51.270
Well, the knowledge
you're privy to is--

00:14:51.270 --> 00:14:54.899
Relax! I'm not gonna go
around blabbing about it.

00:14:54.899 --> 00:14:57.193
Y'know... if it's a
problem with the time machine

00:14:57.193 --> 00:14:58.736
that's got you all
down in the dumps...

00:14:58.736 --> 00:15:01.781
why not try hitting up
ol' John Titor for advice?

00:15:04.534 --> 00:15:07.453
In his earlier posts...
Titor did mention

00:15:07.453 --> 00:15:08.996
that altering the past
would change the...

00:15:08.996 --> 00:15:12.542
the "divergence number,"
I believe he called it...

00:15:12.542 --> 00:15:15.253
which would in
turn shift existence

00:15:15.253 --> 00:15:16.671
onto a different world-line.

00:15:17.588 --> 00:15:19.757
Any memories from
the previous world-line

00:15:19.757 --> 00:15:21.175
that don't agree
with the new reality...

00:15:21.175 --> 00:15:25.304
are basically overwritten with
the non-conflicting memories

00:15:25.304 --> 00:15:27.849
they would have experienced.

00:15:27.849 --> 00:15:29.892
The D-mail tossed
us from a world-line

00:15:29.892 --> 00:15:32.019
in which Rukako didn't
buy a lottery ticket

00:15:32.019 --> 00:15:35.273
onto one in which he did.

00:15:35.273 --> 00:15:39.277
And the past changed
to reflect this new track.

00:15:39.277 --> 00:15:41.654
In this world, we never
sent the winning numbers

00:15:41.654 --> 00:15:43.239
for third prize back in time.

00:15:45.783 --> 00:15:47.285
It isn't that they
don't remember it...

00:15:47.285 --> 00:15:51.372
to them, it never
actually transpired.

00:15:53.499 --> 00:15:55.334
Yet I remember everything...

00:15:55.334 --> 00:15:57.420
But how is that possible?

00:16:03.092 --> 00:16:04.635
Aw, balls! Nae!

00:16:04.635 --> 00:16:05.428
Whatever you do,

00:16:05.428 --> 00:16:08.681
don't tell your daddy I was
slacking off out here, okay?!

00:16:08.681 --> 00:16:10.641
Only if you let me
ride your bike later!

00:16:10.641 --> 00:16:11.976
Got yourself a deal!

00:16:13.895 --> 00:16:16.063
Hey...! Frankenstein!

00:16:16.063 --> 00:16:17.857
Good luck with
that stuff upstairs.

00:16:17.857 --> 00:16:19.567
Oh... thanks...

00:16:22.195 --> 00:16:24.238
Son of a...!

00:16:24.238 --> 00:16:25.615
Yay, you're home!

00:16:25.615 --> 00:16:26.490
Okabe!

00:16:26.490 --> 00:16:28.701
What the hell were you
doing out here with my kid?!

00:16:28.701 --> 00:16:29.160
Huh?!

00:16:29.160 --> 00:16:31.329
My good Mr. Braun,
I've no idea what you're--!

00:16:31.329 --> 00:16:32.371
Don't lie to me!

00:16:32.371 --> 00:16:33.873
That's my baby
girl you're eying,

00:16:33.873 --> 00:16:35.583
so don't think you can
run your experiments

00:16:35.583 --> 00:16:37.501
on her up there in
that creepy lab of yours!

00:16:37.501 --> 00:16:39.462
How dare you
insinuate I would stoop

00:16:39.462 --> 00:16:41.047
to using a child as a lab rat!

00:16:41.047 --> 00:16:42.715
Why don't you ask
Suzuha what we were doing.

00:16:42.715 --> 00:16:43.841
She was out here with us!

00:16:43.841 --> 00:16:45.092
Say what?

00:16:45.092 --> 00:16:46.427
Is that the truth, honey?

00:16:46.427 --> 00:16:47.762
Uh huh, she was out here--

00:16:47.762 --> 00:16:49.680
but she definitely
wasn't slacking off!

00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:50.890
She wasn't, huh...?!

00:16:50.890 --> 00:16:53.100
Why you lazy good-for-nothing!

00:16:53.100 --> 00:16:54.185
I'm making a break for it!

00:16:54.185 --> 00:16:55.603
What the hell am
I paying you for?!

00:16:55.603 --> 00:16:58.481
All ya do is goof off!
Look at this!

00:16:58.481 --> 00:16:59.982
You haven't even
started on this repair!

00:16:59.982 --> 00:17:02.026
I... I won't do it again!

00:17:11.661 --> 00:17:13.829
Due to unforeseen circumstances,

00:17:13.829 --> 00:17:15.706
I'm calling off today's
Phone Wave test...

00:17:15.706 --> 00:17:17.500
Go home, you guys.

00:17:20.836 --> 00:17:22.296
Okarin...?

00:17:28.344 --> 00:17:30.513
Hey... Didn't you
hear me, Assistant...?

00:17:30.513 --> 00:17:32.431
You're free to go.

00:17:32.431 --> 00:17:34.058
Just doing a little thinking.

00:17:34.058 --> 00:17:37.144
Oh yes... You'd rather sit there

00:17:37.144 --> 00:17:39.397
and stare at my back than
return to the gilded cage

00:17:39.397 --> 00:17:41.566
of your state room--right,
Little Miss Moneybags?

00:17:41.566 --> 00:17:43.484
Quit calling me
that stupid name.

00:17:43.484 --> 00:17:46.028
I'm composing a very
important message here...

00:17:46.028 --> 00:17:48.864
If you insist on loitering,
do try to keep your inarticulate

00:17:48.864 --> 00:17:51.701
brain-starved moaning
to a minimum, Zombie.

00:17:53.411 --> 00:17:56.497
Oh goody. We're back to
my least favorite nickname.

00:18:08.718 --> 00:18:09.969
You're like a schoolgirl,

00:18:09.969 --> 00:18:13.180
waiting for that cute
boy to write back.

00:18:13.180 --> 00:18:15.349
Speaking from
experience, are we...?

00:18:18.102 --> 00:18:19.270
What's up, anyway...?

00:18:19.270 --> 00:18:22.148
Who're you texting?

00:18:22.148 --> 00:18:23.399
John Titor.

00:18:23.399 --> 00:18:24.608
Huh?

00:18:45.796 --> 00:18:46.881
Daru?

00:18:46.881 --> 00:18:48.049
What's going on?

00:18:48.049 --> 00:18:49.425
Okarin--thank God!

00:18:49.425 --> 00:18:52.261
Look, I just realized
I've made a terrible mistake!

00:18:52.261 --> 00:18:54.638
What was it...?! Talk, man!

00:18:54.638 --> 00:18:58.684
It's all... all my fault...

00:18:58.684 --> 00:19:00.686
I left my wallet
back at the lab!

00:19:00.686 --> 00:19:01.354
What?

00:19:01.354 --> 00:19:03.522
Yeah! And Queen May's
shut its doors to me!

00:19:03.522 --> 00:19:05.691
I hate to ask, but
could you maybe--?

00:19:08.152 --> 00:19:10.112
Too-too-roo! Hi, Okarin.

00:19:10.112 --> 00:19:12.156
Oh, hello there, Mayuri.

00:19:13.574 --> 00:19:15.284
Daru's gonna be hitting
you up for money...

00:19:15.284 --> 00:19:17.536
You don't have to give
him anything though, okay?

00:19:17.536 --> 00:19:18.704
Okie-dokie...

00:19:18.704 --> 00:19:21.665
But I called to see if you
were feeling any better.

00:19:21.665 --> 00:19:24.001
If you're not, then I give
you permission to hug

00:19:24.001 --> 00:19:27.755
my oopa cushion for as long
as it takes to cheer you up!

00:19:29.548 --> 00:19:31.300
You know what,
I may just do that...

00:19:31.300 --> 00:19:33.052
You have a good night, okay?

00:19:33.052 --> 00:19:35.846
Don't forget to hug it, okay?

00:19:39.225 --> 00:19:41.394
Huh. You're all smiles again.

00:19:49.068 --> 00:19:50.361
It's him!

00:19:51.404 --> 00:19:52.780
I received your message...

00:19:52.780 --> 00:19:54.573
From what you describe,

00:19:54.573 --> 00:19:57.034
I can only conclude
that you altered the past

00:19:57.034 --> 00:19:59.703
and shifted the world line.

00:19:59.703 --> 00:20:01.914
Your scenario does
puzzle me, though.

00:20:01.914 --> 00:20:04.500
I don't understand how
you have retained memories

00:20:04.500 --> 00:20:07.962
of your original past.
It is problematic.

00:20:09.380 --> 00:20:10.631
I swear it's the truth...

00:20:10.631 --> 00:20:13.426
This has happened
to me twice now...

00:20:13.426 --> 00:20:15.344
What do you make of it?

00:20:15.344 --> 00:20:16.429
I don't know.

00:20:16.429 --> 00:20:19.181
In the version of 2036
from which I hail,

00:20:19.181 --> 00:20:20.891
the idea of using e-mail

00:20:20.891 --> 00:20:24.562
to alter past events
hasn't been explored.

00:20:24.562 --> 00:20:26.063
The concept of altering the past

00:20:26.063 --> 00:20:29.442
and shifting the world-line
is nothing new to us.

00:20:29.442 --> 00:20:31.235
That said, it operates within

00:20:31.235 --> 00:20:32.862
limits we've
thought were absolute.

00:20:32.862 --> 00:20:34.697
No one has ever
been known to maintain

00:20:34.697 --> 00:20:39.452
their memories across world
lines and observe their changes.

00:20:39.452 --> 00:20:40.744
Even so...

00:20:40.744 --> 00:20:44.373
Kyouma... It might be
that you have that ability.

00:20:47.084 --> 00:20:48.961
You might be the one person...

00:20:48.961 --> 00:20:53.007
who can guide the world
beyond 1% divergence.

00:20:54.633 --> 00:20:55.551
"Guide the world?!"

00:20:55.551 --> 00:20:57.428
What is he talking about?!

00:21:00.514 --> 00:21:03.142
What is this 1% divergence
you're talking about...?!

00:21:03.142 --> 00:21:06.020
And what lies beyond
it that's so important?!

00:21:22.870 --> 00:21:25.331
Beyond it lies true freedom.

00:21:25.331 --> 00:21:26.790
Your future is condemned

00:21:26.790 --> 00:21:29.752
to dystopia unless that
barrier can be crossed.

00:21:31.754 --> 00:21:33.798
My goal is to save the future...

00:21:33.798 --> 00:21:37.676
And you may be the
only one who can do it.

00:21:39.970 --> 00:21:43.140
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

00:21:43.140 --> 00:21:43.974
No... It doesn't make any sense.

00:21:43.974 --> 00:21:45.976
This has got to be
some kind of mistake...

00:21:45.976 --> 00:21:48.812
How can I... save the future...?

00:21:48.812 --> 00:21:50.439
That's absurd...

00:22:01.617 --> 00:22:04.787
Kyouma... I ask you...

00:22:06.497 --> 00:22:08.415
...to be... our savior.

